	   <tr><td colspan=2>I think your description of group experience is on the money, but not how it affects party members. <br><br>Take for example your troll and halfling duo. If they play from birth only together...yes, the halfling will 'out level' the troll. BUT if instead they 'solo to 6'...then start grouping, they will stay at or about the same level for ever. The troll (who will need ALOT more exp to get to 6) will take about 66% of the exp from each kill to the halflings 33%...and all of the sudden, they both hit 7 at about the same time.<br><br>So in general if one party member get's a 'bubble' of experience...all members will get a bubble of exp...that the troll shadow knight got most of the exp and the halfling warrior got the least will be hidden in the bubble ;)<br><br>Krilmar<br>Troll Shadow Knight (YEA...give ME a bigger cut!)<br>Torv<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
