	   <tr><td colspan=2>A few points you should be aware of.<br><br>Basically the conclusions in the above post DO NOT follow from the data.<br><br>1) Death penalties ARE NOT related to YOUR experience ONLY your LEVEL.<br>2) Hybrids DO take a disproportionate proportion of XP.<br>3) Hell Levels DO make people take extra xp though NOT in a very simple way.<br><br><br>NB Before I go into this I would like to say that I don't discriminate on the basis of xp and it is FAR MORE IMPORTANT to have people who play well than people who will take less xp.<br><br><br>1) Abashi actually gave the truth on this one eventually. The xp lost on death is a certain proportion of the xp a HUMAN WARRIOR would need to reach your next level.&nbsp;&nbsp;I don't know if the porportion changes at hell lvls though. <br>NB CLEARLY you do not lose 10% of total xp at lvl50 as this would be a couple of whole LEVELS.<br><br>2) XP is distributed among the group based on each character's total xp so far. Hybrids require more xp to level and thus WILL ALREADY have more xp than another class (proportional to lvl of course). As they already have more xp they take a higher proportion of the xp from the group. It's that simple. <br>The whole "Hybrids take more xp" thing ONLY AROSE when this data became available from Hackerquest and it is a sad but absolutely true statement.<br>(well if the first statement in 5 of the above post -which has been doing the rounds rather a lot :( is true as I believe it is).<br><br>3) This is much the same point as 2. People who have passed through a hell lvl have more xp than people who don't so those who care about such things should be wary of grouping with people who have passed through a hell lvl they haven't. <br><br>Being actually in the hell level does this partly -it increases the effect you experience throughout the game that people who are closer to finishing their level gain more xp than those at teh beginning of their lvl as they have more xp already. <br>(those who really care about getting the most xp should always try to group with people earlier in the lvl than themselves; just after levelling is the best time to solo xp-wise)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
